Communicated by:
ProMED

[This week's report has 3 countries reporting AFP cases associated with cVDPV - cVDPV2 in DR Congo and Nigeria and cVDPV3 in Israel. Other areas with documented cVDPVs through environmental sampling include cVDPV2 in Cote d'Ivoire and Mauritania, and cVDPV3 in the Palestinian Authority.

Unfortunately the charts showing the virus isolates and date of most recent isolate by source (AFP case other humans (non-AFP infected) and environmental samples) for WPVs and cVDPVs for this past week (as of 9 Mar 2022) have not been posted as yet (see https://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/this-week/circulating-vaccine-derived-poliovirus/). It would be interesting to see the time table of positive samples... did the ESs pre-date the identification of the AFP case (the answer seems to be yes reading between the lines) and did the positive ESs in the Palestinian Authority precede, follow or were basically chronologically the same?

According to the Polio Eradication Initiative website, as of 1 Mar 2022 there had only been 2 countries reporting isolation of cVDPV3 since 2016 - China (positive ES 25 Jan 2021) and Somalia (positive AFP case 7 Sep 2018). Unless there has been undetected circulation in those countries for 1 and 3 years, respectively, it is highly likely this virus is a new outbreak in the region.

Other information not mentioned is whether the cVDPV3 isolates in the Palestinian Authority are genetically related to those identified in Israel.

A map showing Israel and the Palestinian Authority can be found at: https://www.nationsonline.org/oneworld/map/israel_map.htm.

A map showing the locations of each confirmed case of polio worldwide in the past 12 months can be found at https://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/. One can see cases of cVDPV in a band across Africa and in Israel, Ukraine, Tajikistan, Afghanistan and Pakistan, cVDPV1 in Madagascar and Yemen, and WPV1 in Afghanistan and Pakistan. - Mod.MPP]

******
[2] Israel, Palestine cVDPV3
Date: Thu 10 Mar 2022
Source: Polio Eradication Initiative [edited]
https://polioeradication.org/news-post/circulating-vaccine-derived-poliovirus-confirmed-in-israel-and-occupied-palestinian-territory/


Circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus confirmed in Israel and the occupied Palestinian territory
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
On Monday [7 Mar 2022], a case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 3 (cVDPV3) was confirmed in an unvaccinated girl aged 3 years and 9 months in Israel. The girl had developed acute flaccid paralysis and upon testing of her stool, poliovirus was confirmed. Further testing of the poliovirus isolated from the girl revealed genetic links to VDPV3-strains detected in environmental samples collected from sites in in Israel and the occupied Palestinian territory between September 2021 and January 2022. These isolates, previously classified as ambiguous VDPV3, have now been reclassified as circulating VDPV3 (cVDPV3). This confirms an outbreak of cVDPV3 in both Israel and the occupied Palestinian territory.

Local health authorities are conducting field, epidemiological and virological investigations, to determine more clearly the source and origin of the isolated virus, and potential risk of further spread associated with it.

Experts from the headquarters, regional and country offices of the Global Polio Eradication Initiative (GPEI) partnership, which includes WHO, Rotary International (RI), the US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC), the United Nations Children's Fund (UNICEF), Bill & Melinda Gates Foundation (BMGF) and the Global Alliance for Vaccine and Immunization (GAVI), are working together to help ensure an appropriate response and cessation of this outbreak.

Detection of this cVDPV3 underscores the importance of strong disease surveillance and high population immunity levels, in order to minimize the risk and consequences of any poliovirus introduction or emergence.

The GPEI partnership urges all health authorities to enhance surveillance for poliovirus and implement enhanced vaccination response to prevent further transmission, so that no child is at risk of lifelong paralysis from a disease that can so easily be prevented. GPEI is committed to assisting the health authorities in their efforts to stop the cVDPV3 outbreak.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED

[Our thanks to Helen Branswell for alerting us to the identification of cVDPV3 as the causative virus in this event. We await further information on the provenance of the cVDPV3 identified. (see Mod comment following section 1). - Mod.MPP]
